Sentencas: Pr2CuO4-xCe0.9Gd0.1O1.95 (PCO-xCGO, x = 0, 10, 20, 30, 40, 50 wt%) composite cathodes were investigated for potential application in intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of Pr2CuO4-based composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The effect of different sintering temperature on the microstructure and electrochemical performance of the composite cathode was observed.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of Pr2CuO4-based composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) mechanism was analyzed by the electrochemical impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of Pr2CuO4-based composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was found that the addition of CGO in PCO cathode significantly reduced the polarization resistance (R-p).
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of Pr2CuO4-based composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lowest R-p of 0.12 Omega cm(2) for PCO-40CGO composite cathode at 700 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of Pr2CuO4-based composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Oxygen partial pressure dependence study indicates that the charge transfer process is rate-limiting step for ORR on the electrode.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of Pr2CuO4-based composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum exchange current density i(0) of the PCO-40CGO composite cathode was 15.10 mA cm(2) at 700 degrees C. All above properties indicate that the PCO-40CGO composite is a promising cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrochemical investigation of Pr2CuO4-based composite cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
